new beginnings water in the west search search this site stanford university water in the west about people research publications news events new beginnings water in the west is a joint program of the woods institute for the environment and the bill lane center for the american west at stanford university contact us home new beginnings dear friends and colleagues with the start of the new year comes the beginning of a new endeavor after 15 years with american rivers serving most recently as senior vice president for conservation i am pleased to embark on a new venture as executive director for water in the west at stanford university a joint venture between the woods institute for the environment and the bill lane center for the american west water in the west engages in strategically designed research dialogues and policy initiatives to develop and demonstrate solutions to the major water challenges facing the western us i was fortunate to have my father accompany me on the 3000 mile drive from washington dc and we had the opportunity to view first hand part of the great landscape of the american west to pass the time on the long drive we listened to all 14 discs of wallace stegner s unabridged beyond the 100 th meridian a wonderfully written comprehensive biography of john wesley powell and an early evaluation on the place of water in the west the conclusion of the narrative happened to coincide with our arrival at the south rim of the grand canyon a stunning and marvelous twist of fate having contemplated some of the powell's visionary observations and heroics and thoroughly enjoyed the prose of stegner one of the west's great writers and advocates we passed las vegas los angeles and the san joaquin valley some of the places at the very heart of the west's battle over water we arrived to be greeted by a la nina event who's affect has provided almost fairytale weather but which is also contributing to one of the driest winters in almost forty years quite a start i look forward to working with colleagues new and old to contribute to the many challenges we face in managing water in the west please don t hesitate to call or write if you re interested sincerely andrew fahlund executive director water in the west a joint program of the stanford woods institute for the environment and the bill lane center for the american west 473 via ortega mc 4205 room 211 stanford ca 94305 afahlund stanford edu 650 724 8823 w 202 487 6659 c if there is magic on this planet it is contained in water loren eiseley last modified thu 12 jan 2012 at 16 37 add new comment project partners woods institute for the environment creating practical solutions for people and the planet bill lane center for the american west advancing scholarly and public understanding of the past present and future of western north america user login bill lane center for the american west woods institute for the enivronment stanford university
